
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-clean` baraye pak kardan va moratab kardane cartridge-haye printer-haye HP estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta keyfiyat chap ra behtar konid agar rang-ha kharab chap mishavand ya khotooti dar chap dide mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-clean -i`  --> 🖥️ Namayesh dastgah-haye (devices) HP-ye mojood va entekhab yek device baraye tamiz kardan.
    🔹 `hp-clean -g`  --> 🧹 Tamiz kardane cartridge ba estefade az gozine-haye pishfarz (default).
    🔹 `hp-clean -l<level>`  --> 🧼 Set kardane sathe tamizkari. `<level>` mitavanad `basic`, `normal` ya `thorough` bashad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-clean -i

    🔹 List kardane printer-haye HP va entekhab printeri ke mikhahid tamiz konid.

    $ hp-clean -g

    🔹 Shoro kardane tamizkari ba gozine-haye pishfarz.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-clean -lthorough -i

    🔹  In dastoor printer ra ba sathe "thorough" tamiz mikonad, bad az entekhab device az liste namayesh dade shode.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-clean` command is used to clean and maintain the print cartridges of HP printers. It helps to improve print quality when colors are printing poorly, or lines appear in the printouts.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-clean -i`  --> 🖥️ Display available HP devices and select one to clean.
    🔹 `hp-clean -g`  --> 🧹 Clean the cartridge using default options.
    🔹 `hp-clean -l<level>`  --> 🧼 Set the cleaning level.  `<level>` can be `basic`, `normal`, or `thorough`.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-clean -i

    🔹 List HP printers and select the printer you want to clean.

    $ hp-clean -g

    🔹 Start cleaning with default options.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-clean -lthorough -i

    🔹 This command cleans the printer at the "thorough" level, after selecting the device from the displayed list.

